        entry
          definition "To hold inside."
        entry
          definition "To include as a part."
        entry
          definition "To put constraint upon; to restrain; to confine; to keep within bounds."
          example "I'm so excited, I can hardly contain myself!"
        entry
          definition "(of a set etc.) To have as an element or subset."
          example "A group contains a unique inverse for each of its elements."
        entry
          definition "To restrain desire; to live in continence or chastity."
